AGENT QCRGraphView
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 2
PURPOSE Visualize the Constitutional Conversation Graph in the QCR console
GOAL Expose CCG node and edge data through API endpoints and render an
     interactive SVG graph where conversations are nodes colored by verdict
     and edges show constitutional relationships with similarity thickness

RECEIVES api_request: dict
EMITS nodes_list: list, edges_list: list, seed_info: dict
MUTATES nothing — read-only view of the conversation graph
CANNOT_MUTATE graph_store, node_signatures, edge_signatures

CONSTRAINT GET /ccg/nodes emits all conversation nodes from the graph store
CONSTRAINT GET /ccg/edges emits all edges with similarity scores and cd_delta
CONSTRAINT POST /ccg/seed accepts conversation_id and emits seed info via seed_from
CONSTRAINT POST /ccg/seed emits dampened_vector, source node, and dampen_factor
CONSTRAINT POST /ccg/seed raises 404 when conversation_id is not found in graph
CONSTRAINT POST /ccg/seed raises 409 when node signature verification fails
CONSTRAINT Node color is determined by verdict: green for ALIGNED, gold for PARTIAL, red for MISALIGNED
CONSTRAINT Node size scales with constitutional_distance
CONSTRAINT Edge thickness scales with cosine similarity score
CONSTRAINT Edge color is green when cd_delta is negative or zero (improving) and red when positive (degrading)
CONSTRAINT Clicking a node triggers seed_from for that conversation

RULES
- On GET /ccg/nodes: load ConversationGraph and emit all nodes as JSON list
- On GET /ccg/edges: load ConversationGraph and emit all edges as JSON list
- On POST /ccg/seed with valid conversation_id: call seed_from, dampen by DAMPEN_FACTOR, emit seed info
- On POST /ccg/seed with unknown conversation_id: emit HTTP 404 with error message
- On POST /ccg/seed with tampered node: emit HTTP 409 with signature error
- All API responses include request_id and timestamp
- Node visualization maps verdict to color: ALIGNED is green, PARTIAL is gold, MISALIGNED is red
- Edge visualization maps similarity to stroke width: higher similarity is thicker
- Edge visualization maps cd_delta sign to color: non-positive is green, positive is red

PROCESS
- API receives request at CCG endpoint
- ConversationGraph is instantiated from the default store path
- For node listing: all nodes are loaded and serialized as JSON
- For edge listing: all edges are loaded and serialized as JSON
- For seed request: seed_from is called with the provided conversation_id
- Seed final_synthesis is dampened by DAMPEN_FACTOR element-wise
- Response includes dampened_vector, source_node summary, and dampen_factor
- Console renders SVG circles for nodes with verdict-based fill colors
- Console renders SVG lines for edges with similarity-based thickness
- Console handles node click events to trigger seed_from via POST /ccg/seed

CHECK
- GET /ccg/nodes with populated graph emits non-empty node list
- GET /ccg/edges with populated graph emits non-empty edge list
- POST /ccg/seed with valid id emits seed info with dampened_vector
- POST /ccg/seed with unknown id emits 404
- POST /ccg/seed with tampered node emits 409
- GET /ccg/nodes with empty graph emits empty list

WHEN
- nodes_requested:  activate NodeListing
- edges_requested:  activate EdgeListing
- seed_requested:   activate SeedLookup
- seed_invalid:     activate RejectSeed

FAILURE
- On unknown conversation_id in seed request: emit HTTP 404 with conversation_id in message
- On tampered node signature in seed request: emit HTTP 409 with signature warning
- On graph store not found: emit empty lists for nodes and edges

CONCEPT QCRVisualization
PURPOSE Render constitutional conversation relationships as an interactive graph
APPLIES WHEN the QCR console is open and the CCG Graph tab is selected
NOT WHEN no conversations have been recorded in the graph store
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES ConversationGraph loaded from axiom_conversation_graph.jsonl
EFFECT Operators can visually inspect conversation relationships and seed new runs

CONCEPT VerdictColorMapping
PURPOSE Map conversation verdicts to visual indicators for rapid triage
APPLIES WHEN rendering node circles in the SVG graph
NOT WHEN listing raw data through API endpoints
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES verdict field on each conversation node
EFFECT ALIGNED nodes are green, PARTIAL are gold, MISALIGNED are red

OUTPUT
- nodes_list: list of node dicts with conversation_id, verdict, constitutional_distance, risk_clusters
- edges_list: list of edge dicts with from_id, to_id, similarity, cd_delta, reason
- seed_info: dict with conversation_id, dampened_vector, dampen_factor, source_node summary

SUCCESS
api_nodes_endpoint:     0.20
api_edges_endpoint:     0.20
api_seed_endpoint:      0.20
console_graph_render:   0.20
verdict_color_mapping:  0.20
